This species appears to be unique, in particular reference to the development of the labial palpi in the nymph (
Dominguez et al. 2001
) and the subgenital plate in the male imago. The wide projections of the styliger plate are fused into a single structure (Fig. 6d), as mentioned in the discussion of Hydrosmilodon gilliesae (see above), which readily distinguishes Leentvaaria palpalis from all the other members of the complex.
